Auction! Today’s color up in the block is @moltenaura Gold Amethyst. Gold Amethyst is a beautiful rich purple. The color starts off as blue and then strikes when hot to a deep amethyst color. There is a lot of gold in this color making is extremely expensive but worth it! It’s very user friendly, a little stiff but one of the easier of the new colors to come from MA. It looks beautiful blown out of solid. Work hot and turn up the kiln a little to avoid cracking. I run my kiln at 1060 pretty much all the time and haven’t had issues.
